### 🟡 PILLAR 3: ModelSecOps — `src/model_sec/` (Phases 12–16)

**Goal:** The model is guilty until proven innocent. Every model must pass adversarial, bias, and compliance checks before deployment.

```
evaluate.py          (Phase 12: K-fold eval, loads from MLflow or local pickle)
    → bias_audit.py      (Phase 13: Slice model on age/income cohorts, 15% disparity gate)
    → live_bias_fix.py   (Inference-time debiasing via threshold adjustment)
    → regret_minimizer.py (Ethical regret minimization via online learning)
    → intersectional_bias.py (Multi-dimensional fairness: age × gender × region)
    → proxy_bias.py      (Detects hidden proxy variables e.g. zip code → race)
    → fairlearn_audit.py (Fairlearn framework integration)
    → adversarial.py     (ART-based FGSM + PGD attack resilience testing)
    → chaos_test.py      (Random layer removal / weight noise injection)
    → poisoning_guard.py (Detects training data poisoning via influence functions)
    → garak_scan.py      (LLM vulnerability scanner for prompt injection, jailbreak)
    → counterfactuals.py (DiCE-based counterfactual explanations)
    → compliance_filing.py (Auto-generates regulatory filings: EU AI Act, SOC2)
    → model_card.py      (Generates standardized model cards)
    → omni_governance.py (Phase 25: Final governance gate — aggregates all audit reports)
    → zkp_guard.py       (Zero-Knowledge Proof for privacy-preserving inference)
    → enclave.py         (Confidential Computing simulation)
    → monotonicity.py    (Verifies prediction monotonicity constraints)
```

**Key Connection:** `bias_audit.py` is called by `main.py` after `evaluate.py`. Its output (pass/fail) feeds `omni_governance.py` which is the final phase-25 absolute gate.

