### 🟢 PILLAR 4: DevSecOps — `src/devsecops/` (Phases 17–21)

**Goal:** Make the codebase and supply chain untainted. Self-heal, red-team, and harden before deployment.

```
security.py          (SAST scan + SBOM generation — walks src/ for eval/exec/pickle)
advanced_security.py (JWT validation, HTTPS enforcement, rate limiting simulation)
zero_trust.py        (mTLS, service mesh, zero-trust policy enforcement)
vault_manager.py     (HashiCorp Vault: rotates secrets, never hardcodes keys)
agent_audit.py       (Audits autonomous agent actions for compliance)
trivy_scan.py        (Container vulnerability scanning via Trivy CLI)
dependency_patcher.py(pip-audit + auto-patching of vulnerable dependencies)
self_healing_code.py (AST-based code repair: removes unused vars, fixes syntax)
style_repair.py      (Auto-runs Ruff formatter to fix style violations)
red_team.py          (Automated penetration testing simulation)
pqc_sim.py           (Post-Quantum Cryptography: Kyber/Dilithium simulation)
prompt_sec.py        (Prompt injection defense via Rebuff-style detection)
optimize.py          (TurboQuant: INT8/FP16 quantization + ONNX export)
pruning.py           (Extreme structured/unstructured model pruning)
social_trust.py      (Zero-Knowledge social proof attestation)
```

